happy happy holidays my best friends, i love you very very dearly. more than you could possibly imagine. you are everything to me and i am eternally grateful for the love and support you have shown me, but mostly that you have allowed me to be my most vulnerable self with you & have welcomed me with open hearts. you are so beautiful. i love you i love you i love you.
the holidays can be difficult, and i am here for you always. my DMs are always open. you have my entire heart❣️

i’m gonna be completely honest with you, 2022 was really hard. like fully kicked my ass. there were beautiful things, like the release of Baby Magic, that led me to so many wonderful people & allowed me to connect with you all on a deeper level. but, there were less beautiful things. i got dropped by my management the week after Baby Magic’s release, in a VERY brutal way, which left me reeling for the rest of the year. my trust & heart were broken over and over. i was rejected time and time again, once by a producer i’ve idolized since i was 14, and felt my confidence hit a new low that i’m still recovering from. 
i came to a lot of realizations this year, the biggest one being that people will be cruel sometimes, no matter how hard you try to be good, and that is not your fault! i have spent so much of this year blaming myself for other people’s actions, and so listen when i tell you: you are responsible for you & yours. other people’s actions are not always going to be a reflection of who you are — you know yourself best. you determine who you are. 
thank you for welcoming Baby Magic into the world with open arms. thank you for staying up late at night talking to me in our Discord, thank you for making me laugh when i’m scared shitless on my Twitch streams. thank you for reminding me who i am when i forget. thank you for being vulnerable with me, and for trusting me with your hearts. i love you all so dearly. 
if 2022 was a shit year for you too, i’m sending you massive hugs. let’s make a promise to one another to be brave in 2023, to stand up for ourselves and know what we deserve (and what we do not). i have so much more to share with you, so much more to create, and i hope you will stay by my side throughout this journey. thank you all so much. thank you forever❣️

Thank you for listening!

어제 @captainrock1의 생일을 축하하기 위해 무신사개러지(구 왓챠홀)에서 열린 멋진 음악페스티벌 “경록절”을 맞아 공연을 했습니다. 다른 재능있는 뮤지션들과 함께 공연을 할 수 있어서 너무 영광이었고, 너무나도 멋진 경험이었습니다. 열심히 일해주시고 항상 친절하게 도와주시던 스태프 분들, 하루동안 저를 위해 매니저 역할을 해주신 @hoochus_music, 이런 멋지고 아름다운 기회를 주신 @captainrock1, 그리고 저를 반갑고 친절하게 반겨주신 다른 뮤지션 분들께도 너무 감사드립니다.
 그리고 무엇보다 저에게 관심과 열정, 사랑을 보내주신 멋진 관객여러분들께도 감사드립니다. 어제 공연이후 정말 많은 영감과 감명을 받았습니다. 한국에 곧 다시 한번 방문하여 이 아름다운 나라의 문화를 더 배우고, 여러분들 모두를 또 다시 만났으면 좋겠습니다 ❣️🇰🇷⭐️
✨
✨
yesterday, i played at 경록절 at Musinsa Garage, an amazing music festival celebrating @captainrock1 ‘s birthday! it was an incredible experience, and i felt so honored to perform alongside so many talented artists. 
thank you so much to the festival staff, for working hard and being so helpful, to @hoochus_music for being my manager for the day, to @captainrock1 for letting me be a part of such a beautiful experience, to the other performers, for being so kind and welcoming, but most of all, to the audience for showing me so much love and passion. i feel so inspired after performing yesterday, and so grateful. i hope to come back to Korea soon, so i can meet you all again, and learn more about your beautiful country & culture❣️🇰🇷⭐️
(thank you @yonchris0412 for translating!)
PS: bonus picture of me looking like an absolute dumbass on stage at the end☝🏻😟
